      <div xml:id="pl-l1d15c3">
        <head>Capitulum 3</head>
        <!-- Quomodo a Spiritu sancto etiam Filius sit missus. -->
        <p xml:id="pll1d15c3-d1e3477">Et quod a Spiritu sancto missus sit, ut ait <name ref="#Augustine">Augustinus</name> 
          in eodem, auctoritatibus confirmatur.</p>
        <p xml:id="pll1d15c3-d1e3483">Ipse Christus dicit per <name ref="#Isaias">Isaiam</name>: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3490" source="http://scta.info/resource/is48_16">Nunc misit me Dominus 
              et Spiritus eius.</quote>
            <bibl>Isaias 48:16</bibl>
          </cit>
          De hoc <ref><name ref="#Ambrose">Ambrosius</name> in libro III <title>De Spiritu 
            sancto</title></ref> ita ait: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3506">Quis est, qui dicit: 
              <cit>
                <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3510" source="http://scta.info/resource/is48_16">Misit me Dominus et Spiritus eius,</quote>
                <bibl>Isaias 48:16</bibl>
              </cit>
              nisi qui venit a Patre, ut salvos faceret peccatores,</quote>
            <bibl>Ambrosius, De Spiritu sancto, III, XXX</bibl>
          </cit>
          id est Christus?
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3524">Ergo et Pater Filium misit et Spiritus</quote>
            <bibl>Ambrosius, De Spiritu sancto, III, XXX</bibl>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="pll1d15c3-d1e3532">Idem in eodem: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3536">Datus est a Patre, ut <title ref="#is">Isaias</title> dicit: 
              <cit>
                <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3543" source="http://scta.info/resource/is9_6">Puer natus est nobis, et Filius datus est nobis.</quote>
                <bibl>Isaias 9:6</bibl>
              </cit>
              Datus est, audeo 
              dicere, et a Spiritu, quia et a Spiritu missus est.</quote>
            <bibl>Ambrosius, De Spiritu sancto, III, c. 2</bibl>
          </cit>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3557">Dicit enim 
              Filius Dei: 
              <cit>
                <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3561" source="http://scta.info/resource/lc4_18"><!-- also 4_19 -->Spiritus Domini super me, propter quod unxit me: 
                  <!-- p. 97 -->
                  evangelizare pauperibus misit me, praedicare captivis remissionem</quote>
                <bibl>Lucas 4:18-19</bibl>
              </cit>
              etc. Quod cum de libro <title ref="#is">Isaiae</title> legeret, ait in Evangelio: 
              <cit>
                <quote xml:id="pll1d15c3-Qd1e3576" source="http://scta.info/resource/lc4_21">Hodie completa est haec Scriptura in auribus vestris,</quote>
                <bibl>Lucas 4:21</bibl>
              </cit>
              ut de se 
              dictum esse significaret. Bene autem dixit, <mentioned>super me;</mentioned> quia quasi 
              filius hominis et unctus est et missus ad praedicandum. Nam secundum 
              divinitatem non super Christum est Spiritus, sed in Christo.</quote>
            <bibl>Ambrosius, De Spiritu sancto, III, c. 1, n. 1, 2, 6, passim.</bibl>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="pll1d15c3-d1e3593">Ecce his verbis ostendit <name ref="#Ambrose">Ambrosius</name>, Filium esse missum 
          et datum nobis non tantum a patre, sed etiam a Spiritu sancto.</p>
      </div>
